{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Troubleshooting"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"FFI Module Errors","anchor":"FFI-Module-Errors","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On some versions of macOS, when Xcode is installed,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"there is a conflict between the FFI library module","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"available through Xcode and the command line tools.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This typically results in an error such as"}]},{"syntax":null,"code":["\/Applications\/Xcode.app\/Contents\/Developer\/Platforms\/MacOSX.platform\/Developer\/SDKs\/MacOSX14.2.sdk\/usr\/include\/ffi\/module.modulemap:1:8: error: redefinition of module 'FFI'","module FFI [system] {","       ^","\/Library\/Developer\/CommandLineTools\/SDKs\/MacOSX13.sdk\/usr\/include\/ffi\/module.modulemap:1:8: note: previously defined here","module FFI [system] [extern_c] {","       ^","error: fatalError"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A way to resolve this is to remove the Command Line Tools.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, you can temporarily rename the CommandLineTools folder, i.e."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["sudo mv \/Library\/Developer\/CommandLineTools{,.orig}"],"syntax":null},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Later you can move the folder back:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["sudo mv \/Library\/Developer\/CommandLineTools{.orig,}"]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Missing-gir-Files","text":"Missing `.gir` Files"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you get an error such as"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["Girs located at","Cannot open '\/GLib-2.0.gir': No such file or directory"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Make sure that you have the relevant "},{"code":"gobject-introspection","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" packages installed (as per the Pre-requisites section), including their ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".gir"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".pc"},{"type":"text","text":" files."}]},{"anchor":"Old-Swift-toolchain-or-Xcode","text":"Old Swift toolchain or Xcode","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If, when you run "},{"code":"swift build","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", you get a ","type":"text"},{"code":"Segmentation fault (core dumped)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or circular dependency error such as"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["warning: circular dependency detected while parsing pangocairo: harfbuzz -> freetype2 -> harfbuzz"],"syntax":null},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"this probably means that your Swift toolchain is too old, particularly on Linux."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Make sure the latest toolchain is the one that is found when you run the Swift compiler (see above)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you get an older version, make sure that the right version of the swift compiler is found first in your ","type":"text"},{"code":"PATH","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":".  On macOS, use xcode-select to select and install the latest version, e.g.:"}]},{"syntax":null,"code":["sudo xcode-select -s \/Applications\/Xcode.app","xcode-select --install"],"type":"codeListing"}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"role":"article","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Troubleshooting"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This section shows some common errors you might encounter and how to fix them."}],"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/troubleshooting"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib","abstract":[]}}}